    "119762368": {
      "title": "Interpolation by piecewise-linear radial basis functions",
      "abstract": "Abstract In the two-dimensional plane, a set of nodes x 1 , x 2 , …, x n is given. It is desired to interpolate arbitrary data given at the nodes by a linear combination of the functions h i ( x ) = ∥ x − x i ∥. Here the norm is the l 1 -norm. For this purpose, one can employ the space PL of all continuous piecewise-linear functions on the rectangular grid generated by the nodes. Interpolation at the nodes by this larger space is quite easy. By adding an appropriate PL -function that vanishes on the nodes, we can obtain the linear combination of h 1 , h 2 , …, h n that interpolates the data. This algorithm is much more efficient than the straightforward method of simply solving the linear system of equations ∑ c j h j ( x i ) = d i ."
    }
